This topic describes the changes in Tanzu Build Service (commonly known as TBS).

## <a id="1-13-0"></a> v1.13.0

**Release Date: February 29, 2024**

### Breaking changes

- Lifecycle v0.12.0 is the minimum supported version for Tanzu Build Service v1.13.
  Older versions have Platform API v0.7 or earlier, which are not supported by Tanzu Build Service.

- The legacy Cloud Native Buildpack Bill of Materials (CNB BOM) format has been removed.

- kapp based installs are no longer supported. TBS requires kapp-controller to be installed.

- ClusterStores are no longer created by default during install. 
  Buildpacks are now represented by (Cluster)Buildpack resources.

- The TanzunetDependencyUpdater is removed and replaced with a new Dependency Updater with enhanced configuration options

### New Features

- Tanzu Build Service can now generate Supply-chain Levels for Software Artifacts (SLSA) attestations.
  For instructions, see
  [Using Supply-chain Levels for Software Artifacts with Tanzu Build Service](slsa-attestations.md).

- Tanzu UBI and Static builders are now available and you can install them as part
  of the Full dependencies. For instructions, see the `enable_ubi_builder`
  and `enable_startic_builder` fields during [Installation](installing.md#install).

  For the supported languages for these builders, see the [Tanzu Stacks documentation](https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-Tanzu-Buildpacks/services/tanzu-buildpacks/GUID-stacks.html).

- Dependency updates now allow configuration for exactly which dependencies get updated.

  See [Updating Dependencies](updating-deps.html) for more info.

- Kp cli now supports configuring `failedBuildHistoryLimit` and `successBuildHistoryLimit` on images

### Product Snapshot

Tanzu Build Service v1.13.0 includes the following components:

- [kpack v0.13.0](https://github.com/buildpacks-community/kpack/releases/tag/v0.13.0)
- [kpack cli v0.13.0](https://github.com/buildpacks-community/kpack-cli/releases/tag/v0.13.0)
- [CNB lifecycle v0.17.3](https://github.com/buildpacks/lifecycle/releases/tag/v0.17.3)

Tanzu Build Service supports and uses [Tanzu Buildpacks](https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-Tanzu-Buildpacks/index.html).

### Product Dependencies

You can install Tanzu Build Service on any Kubernetes cluster v1.27 or later.

### Upgrade Path

You can upgrade v1.12.x to v1.13.x. For upgrade instructions, follow the procedures in
[Install Tanzu Build Service with kapp controller](installing.html).
